  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div xml:id="AN126.2-kilavi">
          <p type="edition"><l>1. uṇarppuvayiṉ varāvūṭaṟkaṇ talaimakaṉ taṉṉeñciṟkuc colliyatu.</l>
            <l>2. allakuṟippaṭṭu talaimakaṉ taṉṉeñciṟkuc colliyatūumām.</l>
            <l>3. tōḻi piṉṉiṉṟa talaimakaṉ taṉṉeñciṟkuc colliyatu.</l></p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en"><l>1. What HE said to his own heart during a quarrel before he had come [back] to [his] senses.</l>
            <l>2. It is also what HE said to his own heart when led astray by a wrong sign.</l>
            <l>3. What HE who had humbly begged the confidante said to his own heart. </l></p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="AN126.2">
            <lg type="edition">
                <l>niṉvāyc cettu nīpala vuḷḷi</l>
                <l>perumpuṉ paitalai varunta laṉṟiyu</l>
                <l>malaimicait toṭutta malintucela ṉīttan</l>
                <l>talaināṇ māmalar taṇṭuṟait tayaṅkak</l>
                <l>kaṭalkarai melikkuṅ kāvirip pēryāṟ</l>
                <l>ṟaṟalvār neṭuṅkayat tarunilai kalaṅka</l>
                <l>māliru ṇaṭunāṭ pōkiya taṉṉaiyark</l>
                <l>kālai tanta kaṇaikkōṭṭu vāḷaik</l>
                <l>kavvāṅ kunti yañcoṟ pāṇmaka</l>
                <l>ṇeṭuṅkoṭi nuṭaṅku naṟavumali maṟukiṟ</l>
                <l>paḻañcey nelliṉ mukavai koḷḷāḷ</l>
                <l>kaḻaṅkuṟaḻ muttamoṭu naṉkalam porūum</l>
                <l>payaṅkeḻu vaippiṟ palvē levvi</l>
                <l>nayampuri naṉmoḻi yaṭakkavu maṭaṅkāṉ</l>
                <l>poṉṉiṇar naṟumalarp puṉṉai veḵkit</l>
                <l><supplied>ti</supplied>tiyaṉoṭu poruta vaṉṉi pōla</l>
                <l>viḷikuvai kollō nīyē kiḷiyeṉac</l>
                <l>ciṟiya miḻaṟṟuñ cevvāyp periya</l>
                <l>kayaleṉa vamartta vuṇkaṭ puyaleṉap</l>
                <l>puṟantāḻ piruḷiya piṟaṅkukura laimpāṉ</l>
                <l>miṉṉē maruṅkuṟ kuṟumakaḷ</l>
                <l>piṉṉilai viṭāa maṭaṅkeḻu neñcē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <l>Besides suffering the great lowly suffering:</l>
                <l>thinking of your truth, you remembering many [things/times], (1f.)</l>
                <l>like Aṉṉi who fought with Titiyaṉ,</l>
                <l>hankering after [his] mastwood trees with fragrant flowers in golden clusters,</l>
                <l>who did not yield although Evvi restrained [him] with good words of acting with affection,</l>
                <l>[Evvi] with many spears of the yield-bringing region, (13-16)</l>
                <l>where they haggle,</l>
                <l>because of the round-finned Vāḷai fish that was brought in the morning</l>
                <l>by her people who had gone at midnight in deep darkness</l>
                <l>to stir up the precious state of the large pond overflowing with black sand</l>
                <l>by the great river of Kāviri that softens the banks of the sea</l>
                <l>so that big blossoms glitter on the cool ghat on the first day</l>
                <l>of the growing, going flood that was brought together on top of the mountain, (3-8)</l>
                <l rend="indent4">about good ornaments along with pearl-like Molucca beans</l>
                <l>with the bard girl with pretty words and a pretty curving belly,</l>
                <l>who does not take [as payment] a measure of paddy from the ancient fields</l>
                <l>in the street abounding in toddy where long flags wave, (9-12)</l>
                <l>will you perish, you? (17)</l>
                <l>Ignorant heart that does not leave off entreating</l>
                <l>the small girl with a waist [thin] as lightning,</l>
                <l>[her] curls hanging down [her] back [and] glistening darkly in five parts,</l>
                <l>[her] kajal eyes, opposed like [two] Kayal fish, rain-like,</l>
                <l>[her] red mouth large that prattles little [words] like a parrot? (17-22)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
